+# Security Patch Notes - @rootio/playwright
+
+## CVE-2025-59288
+
+**Severity:** High
+
+**Description:** Improper verification of cryptographic signatures during browser downloads. The `-k` (--insecure) flag in curl commands bypasses SSL certificate validation, allowing MITM attackers on the same network to intercept and replace browser packages with malicious ones.
+
+## Fix Location
+
+The actual vulnerability exists in `playwright-core`, not in this package (`playwright`).
+
+This package is a thin wrapper that depends on `playwright-core`. The security fix has been applied to:
+
+- **Package:** `@rootio/playwright-core@1.49.0-root.io.1`
+- **Fixed files:** `bin/reinstall_*_mac.sh` scripts
+- **Change:** Removed `-k` flag from curl commands to enforce SSL certificate validation
+
+## Upstream Fix
+
+- **Commit:** https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/commit/72c62d840247d9defd87c6beb0344d456794b570
+- **Fixed in:** playwright v1.55.1+
+
+## Patched by
+Root.io Security Team

